definition.value: An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxy-5-methylhexanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxyheptanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxynonanoyl.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is myristic acid in which the 13-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A monounsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (10Z)-heptadecenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is trans-2-pentadecenoic acid in which the 14-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A pentadecenoic acid in which the olefinic double bond is at position 2 and has E configuration.
An anionic phospholipid arising from deprotonation of all three free phosphate OH groups of 1,2-dipalmitoylglycero-3-phospho-(1'-D-myo-inositol-3'-phosphate); major species at pH 7.

A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,5-bisphosphate(5-) arising from deprotonation of all five free phosphate OH groups of 1,2-dipalmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-D-myo-inositol-3',5'-bisphosphate); major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 5-phosphate(3-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1,2-dipalmitoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-myo-inositol-5'-phosphate); major species at pH 7.3.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is pentadecanoic acid in which the 14-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is (E)-hexadec-2-enoic acid in which the 15-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is hexadecanoic acid in which the 15-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is (2E)-heptadec-2-enoic acid in which the 16-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A heptadecenoic acid in which the olefinic double bond is at the 2-3 position.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is heptadecanoic acid in which the 16-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is (2E)-octadec-2-enoic acid in which the 17-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is octadecanoic acid (stearic acid) in which the 17-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.
An amino-acid residue derived from diphthine methyl ester.

An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is nonadecanoic acid which has been dehydrogenated to introduce a double bond with E configuration between positions 2 and 3 and in which the pro-R hydrogen at position 17 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
A very long-chain fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of tricosanoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of (R)-nicotine arising from selective protonation of the tertiary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (9Z)-tetradecenoyl.
A prostaglandin carboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of prostaglandin D1, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is nonadecanoic acid in which the 18-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.
An O-(S-3-oxoacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (11Z)-3-oxohexadecenoyl.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is trans-2-icosenoic acid in which the pro-R hydrogen at position 19 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
An icosenoic acid in which the double bond is at the 2-3 position and has E configuration.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is arachidic acid acid in which the 19-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.

An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is henicosanoic acid in which a double bond with E configuration has been introduced at the 2-3 position and in which the pro-R hydrogen at position 20 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.
A 20-hydroxyhenicosanoic acid that has R configuration.

An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid ascaroside obtained by formal condensation of the alcoholic hydroxy group of (4R)-4-hydroxypentanoic acid with ascarylopyranose (the alpha anomer). It is a metabolite of the nematodes Caenorhabditis elegans and Pristionchus pacificus.
An (omega-1)-hydroxy fatty acid that is valeric acid in which the 4-pro-R hydrogen is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A monocarboxylic acid in which the carbon of the carboxy group is directly attached to a C=C or C#C bond.
A monounsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (11Z)-3-oxohexadecenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A 4-O-(1H-indol-3-ylcarbonyl)ascaroside derived from (2E,6R)-6-hydroxyhept-2-enoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.
An ascaroside of a hydroxy fatty acid in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the ascarylopyranose moiety has been has been converted into the corresponding 1H-indole-3-carboxylate ester.
An indolyl carboxylate ester resulting from the formal condensation of 1H-indole-3-carboxylic acid with the hydroxy group of any alcohol or phenol.
An organic anionic group derived from molybdenum cofactor(3-).  It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the hydroxy group of L-topaquinone residue. It is the major microspecies at pH 7.3 (according to Marvin v 6.2.0.).
A 4-O-(1H-indol-3-ylcarbonyl)ascaroside derived from (4R)-4-hydroxypentanoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.
A 4-O-(1H-indol-3-ylcarbonyl)ascaroside derived from (8R)-8-hydroxynonanoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.
A thioadenosine that is adenosine in which the hydroxy group at C-5' is replaced by a 3-aminopropyl group.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of dihydromonacolin L acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An O-(S-3-oxoacylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as dihydromonacolin L carboxy.

A member of the class of stilbenoids in which the para-hydrogens of stilbene are replaced by methylamino and 2-{2-[2-((18)F)fluoroethoxy]ethoxy}ethoxy) groups. A positron emission tomography imaging ligand for the detection of amyloid aggregation associated with Alzheimer disease.
